                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0060" view="all">List of linear mixed-effect models employed. <ce:italic>Tmax</ce:italic> and <ce:italic>VPDmax</ce:italic> represents mean maximum temperature and mean maximum VPD respectively, <ce:italic>Canopy cover</ce:italic> represents mean canopy cover based on densiometer data, <ce:italic>Distance</ce:italic> represents distance from forest edge. <ce:italic>Forest category indicates</ce:italic> for; a) Grumsin (CZ = core zone, BZ = buffer zone, NF = non-forest); b) Hainich (CZ = core zone, BZ = buffer zone, ED = forest edge, NF = non-forest agricultural land); c) Kellerwald (CZ<ce:inf loc="post">A</ce:inf> = core zone A, CZ<ce:inf loc="post">B</ce:inf> = core zone B, OF<ce:inf loc="post">A</ce:inf> = open forest A (dead spruce stand), OF<ce:inf loc="post">B</ce:inf> = open forest B (open beech stand), NF<ce:inf loc="post">A</ce:inf> = non-forest A, NF<ce:inf loc="post">B</ce:inf> = non-forest B); d) Serrahn (CZ = core zone, BZ<ce:inf loc="post">C</ce:inf> = pine stand with dense beech understorey, BZ<ce:inf loc="post">B</ce:inf> = pine stand mixed low broadleaved understorey, BZ<ce:inf loc="post">A</ce:inf> = pure pine stand, ED = forest edge, NF = non-forest).</ce:simple-para>
